result.execSummary:
The defendant Patricia Louise Swayka was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Patricia Louise Swayka in court with attorney Michael J Steinle.  Matthew Richard Westphal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy Court Clerk: STW  
Case set for Review Hearing. The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

AS TO COUNT 1 :On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Theft, contrary to Milwaukee County Ordiance 63.042 to which the defendant entered a plea of NO CONTEST.  The Court orders defendant to pay a fine of $200.00 plus costs to be paid by 9-28-2022 or a civil judgment to be entered with tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
NOTE, the State request a 3 month review held in Branch 38  before Judge Wagner.

The parties have agreed to a deferred judgment agreement.The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, pled NO CONTEST and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionaire/Wiaver of Rights and Addendum to Plea Questionaire received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty but WITHHELD entry of Judgement of Conviction.  The Court reviewed the Intake Requirement and Further Conditions with the defendant.  The court approved the Deferred Prosecution Agreement and ordered the proceedings suspended for a period of six months. Case adjourned to Branch 38 for a 3 Month Review Hearing.
Original Information filed.  Copy given to defense counsel who waived reading.  Defendant pled No Contest.

Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing.  Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed.  Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Defense acknowledges receipt of the Information, waives reading and enters a plea of No Contest on behalf of his client.

Defendant Patricia Louise Swayka in court with Attorney Michael J Steinle.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge  Wagner, Branch 38.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT DOES NOT QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.
